//Heal Skill


@800000 = ~Healing Proficiency~
@800001 = ~The healer can use a healer's kit to treat the injuries and afflictions of <PRO_HISHER> allies on the fly.  <PRO_HESHE> heals 5% of targets max hit points, +5% per rank, + <PRO_HISHER> wisdom bonus (max 30% + wisdom bonus at 5 ranks).  Additionally, successfully treated characters will find their healing rate improved (the rate depends upon the number of ranks of the healer; see below).  This ability is not magical, and there is a chance that <PRO_HESHE> cannot help <PRO_HISHER> ally.  The chance of success with a heal check is equal to 50% +5% per rank, plus <PRO_HISHER> Wisdom Bonus (max 95%).  

Especially skilled healers can use a healer's kit to treat any allies that have recently been afflicted with various toxic substances and debilitating magics.  Upon attaining 5 ranks in Heal, <PRO_HESHE> gains the ability to Treat Afflictions.

Treating such afflictions is tricky, however, and the treatment is not always effective.  The chance of success is equal to 10% +5% per rank in healing plus their wisdom bonus. Experts in herbalism are much more effective at treating afflictions.  They receive a +5% bonus to their check for every rank they have in herbalism if they have at least 5 ranks in herbalism. (max 95%)

Treat Wounds

Effect: Heals 5% of target's max hit points, +5% per rank, + the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus).

Chance of Success: 50%, +5% per rank, + the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus).

Special: Accelerated Healing rate:
1 rank: 1 hit point per 16 turns
2 ranks: 1 hit point per 8 turns
3 ranks: 1 hit point per 4 turns
4 ranks: 1 hit point per 2 turns
5+ ranks: 1 hit point per turn.

Untrained: A character can use this skill untrained, though it isn't recommended as they have a chance to harm the target. Note that characters treated by untrained allies do not see an increase in their healing rate.

Effects: Heals 5% of target's max hit points, + the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus).

Chance of Success: 50%, + the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus).

Mishap: 1d8 points of non-lethal damage.

Chance of Mishap: 30%, - the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus).

Treat Affliction

Chance of Success: 10%, +5% per rank in Heal, + the healer's wisdom bonus (i.e. <PRO_HISHER> percentage bonus), + 5% per rank in Herbalism (if the healer has at least 5 ranks in herbalism).

Effect:
5 Ranks: Treat Intoxication, Poison, Blindness and Deafness.
6 Ranks: Treat Diseases.
7 Ranks: Treat Paralysis and Hold.~

